AB  - This paper shows that the remarkable result by Khan and Naqvi that a reduction in the capital rental differential always improves welfare despite the presence of a rigid urban wage can be obtained only for the 2 × 2 Harris-Todaro model. In an extended Harris-Todaro framework incorporating a third specific factor, a decrease in a distortion may not necessarily be welfare improving.
