T1  - Permanent and transitory components of Colombia's real GDP: The over-consumption hypothesis revisited
AU  - Clavijo, Sergio
JO  - Journal of Development Economics
VL  - 38
IS  - 2
SP  - 371
EP  - 382
PY  - 1992
DA  - 1992/04/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(92)90005-T
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030438789290005T
AB  - Cuddington's (1986) ‘over-consumption hypothesis’ is revised by exploring how sensitive the results are to different methods of real-GDP decomposition. Using a different model selection procedure, we adopt an ARIMA specification which leads to have a real-GDP decomposition that lends no support to the over-consumption hypothesis. However, Cuddington's model, also used in recent JDE-paper [Cuddington and Urzua (1989)], could be chosen for avoiding hypersensitivity of the permanent income. How to balance trade-offs between statistical and theoretical criteria in decomposition is an issue that requires further research.
ER  - 

